name Poppy Seed Mousse with Marinated Figs and Almond Sabayon
serves 4
tags dessert

# Poppy seed mousse

- 50 g ground poppy seeds
- 125 ml white port
Reduce the poppy seeds with the port until all the liquid has evaporated. Leave to cool.
-> poppy seed paste

- 2.5 sheets white gelatine
@nodep
Soak in cold water.
-> gelatine

- 100 g white couverture
@nodep
Roughly chop and melt.
-> couverture

- 1 egg
- 20 g apricot jam
- 0.5 vanilla pod
- 0.5 "unwaxed lemon"
- cinnamon
- salt
= poppy seed paste
= gelatine
= couverture
Mix the poppy seed paste with the apricot jam, a pinch each of cinnamon and salt, the
vanilla seeds and the grated lemon zest. Whisk the egg over a hot water bath until foamy.
Squeeze out the gelatine, dissolve in the warm egg mixture, then fold in the couverture
and the poppy seed paste. Leave the cream to set slightly in a cold water bath.

- 200 ml whipping cream
Whip the cream until stiff and fold into the poppy seed mixture. Divide between {4} moulds
(125 ml each), cover and refrigerate for 3-4 hours.
-> poppy seed mousse

# Figs

- 300 g raspberries
- 4 tbsp water
Bring the raspberries and water to a boil, stirring, then pass through a sieve.
-> raspberry purée

- 200 g honey
- 200 ml red wine
- 100 ml cassis
- 1 "unwaxed orange"
- 1 "unwaxed lemon"
- 0.5 vanilla pod
- 1 stalk lemongrass, roughly crushed
- 3 cloves
- 1 cinnamon stick
= raspberry purée
Wash the orange and lemon in hot water, zest and juice. Combine the raspberry purée with
the honey, red wine, cassis, orange and lemon juice and zest, vanilla pod, lemongrass,
cloves and cinnamon stick. Bring to a boil and leave to infuse for 15 minutes.
-> marinade

- 6 "blue figs (approx. 80 g each)"
- 1 tsp cornstarch
= marinade
<p>Wash and dry the figs, trim the stalks. Pierce the figs all over with a wooden skewer
and place in a heatproof dish. Pass the marinade through a sieve over the figs. Cover and
cook in the preheated oven on the second rack from the bottom at 180°C for 15-20
minutes.</p>
<p>Remove the figs. Bring the marinade to a boil, thicken lightly with the cornstarch
dissolved in a little cold water. Return the figs to the marinade and leave to cool
slightly.</p>
-> marinated figs

# Almond sabayon

- 40 g honey
- 50 ml whipping cream
- 50 ml white wine
- 4 egg yolks
- 30 ml almond liqueur
@nodep
Combine all ingredients and whisk over a hot water bath until creamy.
-> almond sabayon

# Plating

= poppy seed mousse
= marinated figs
= almond sabayon
Turn the poppy seed mousses out onto plates. Quarter the figs. Arrange the figs with some
marinade and the almond sabayon around each mousse and serve.
